		<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
								<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Richmond</placeName> <date><sic>oct</sic> 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1829</date></p>
			<p>My Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">after a very <sic>pleasand</sic> passage I arrived here last night 7 o clock<lb/> found Aunt and all our friends in good health&#44; all are pleased with the<lb/> <sic>acount</sic> I gave them about <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> particularly of the kind treat=<lb/>ment I Received of our friend <persName>Mr &amp; Mrs Piexatto</persName> your servt and myself<lb/> wish very much to have it in any power to return the same at any<lb/> time if ever they should come our way so far for myself&#44; but the<lb/> attention paid to you has made an ever lasting impression in my<lb/> mind that never shall be <sic>forgoten</sic>&#44; I am sure you will do all in your<lb/> power to serve them with all your might&#44; my dear <persName>Isaac</persName> I hope you will Try<lb/> To cultivate the friendship of <sic>every body</sic> in your Congregation and not mind<lb/> some few <sic>thinks</sic> which now and then you might <sic>recieve</sic>&#44; never interfere with<lb/> my <sic>differance</sic> between them&#44; but be a peace maker and make them friends<lb/> Remember one kindly to my friends <persName>Mr and Mrs. [&#63;] Philips</persName> to <persName>Mrs Cohin</persName> and<lb/> her worthy sons &amp; Daughters to old <persName>Mrs Philips</persName> my old <sic>acquaintence</sic> <persName>Mrs Hart</persName> Mr &amp; [&#63;]<lb/> from[&#63;] <persName>Mrs Piso</persName> to the Dear girls at our friend <persName>Mr Piexatto</persName> and all the rest of my<lb/> friends in <placeName><sic>philadelphia</sic></placeName> your aunt <persName>Mrs Depass Rina[&#63;] Abby</persName> send <sic>there</sic><lb/> love to you and I Remain your <sic>affectional</sic> uncle and friend</p>
		  <p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">Zalma Rehine</persName></p>
			<p>NB so you turned informer&#44; what tell your Aunt about the girls to be<lb/> sure that was well done I&#39;ll make her be afraid to let me go from home<lb/> without her&#44; take care I shall [&#63;] when ever in my power</p>
		  <p rend="indent(10)">[&#63;] god bless you</p>
			<p>tell <persName>Mrs Piexotto</persName> that I carred[&#63;] the cake all the to <placeName>Richmond</placeName> to treat<lb/> <persName role="author">Mrs Rehine</persName> with her present Aunt was mighty pleased with it<lb/> let us hear from you soon.</p>

			<pb n="2V"/>
			
			<p><persName>Mr Isaac Leeser</persName></p>
			<p>to the care of <persName>Mr A. C. Piexotto</persName></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
